# 2. Create QUICKSTART.md
quickstart = '''# 🚀 Quick Start Guide

Get your OSINT SOC Platform running in 5 minutes.

## Prerequisites

- Ubuntu 22.04 LTS (or similar)
- 16GB RAM minimum (32GB recommended)
- 100GB free disk space
- Docker & Docker Compose installed
- Internet connection

## One-Line Installation

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/YOUR_USERNAME/osint-soc-platform/main/install.sh | sudo bash
```

## Step-by-Step Installation

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/osint-soc-platform.git
cd osint-soc-platform
```

### 2. Configure Environment

```bash
# Copy environment template
cp .env.example .env

# Edit with your settings (change ALL passwords!)
nano .env
```

**Minimum required changes:**
- All database passwords
- Domain name (if not using localhost)
- API keys for external services (optional)

### 3. Run Installation

```bash
sudo ./install.sh
```

This will:
- Install Docker if not present
- Create directory structure
- Generate configuration files
- Pull Docker images
- Start all services

### 4. Start Services

```bash
cd /opt/osint-soc
./scripts/start.sh
```

### 5. Verify Installation

```bash
./scripts/health-check.sh
```

Expected output:
```
✓ Elasticsearch is UP
✓ PostgreSQL is UP
✓ Redis is UP
✓ Wazuh Dashboard is UP
✓ TheHive is UP
✓ Cortex is UP
✓ MISP is UP
✓ OpenCTI is UP
✓ Shuffle is UP
```

## Access Your Services

| Service | URL | Default Credentials |
|---------|-----|---------------------|
| **Wazuh Dashboard** | http://localhost:5601 | admin / SecretPassword |
| **TheHive** | http://localhost:9000 | admin@thehive.local / secret |
| **Cortex** | http://localhost:9001 | Create on first login |
| **MISP** | https://localhost:8443 | admin@admin.test / admin |
| **OpenCTI** | http://localhost:8080 | admin@opencti.local / changeme |
| **Shuffle** | http://localhost:3001 | Create on first login |

## Next Steps

1. **Change Default Passwords**: Access each service and change default credentials
2. **Configure OSINT Feeds**: See [OSINT-FEEDS.md](docs/OSINT-FEEDS.md)
3. **Set Up Automation**: See [AUTOMATION.md](docs/AUTOMATION.md)
4. **Add Wazuh Agents**: Deploy agents to your endpoints

## Troubleshooting

### Services won't start

```bash
# Check logs
docker-compose -f docker/docker-compose.infra.yml logs
docker-compose -f docker/docker-compose.security.yml logs
docker-compose -f docker/docker-compose.osint.yml logs

# Restart services
./scripts/stop.sh
./scripts/start.sh
```

### Out of memory

```bash
# Add swap
sudo fallocate -l 8G /swapfile
sudo chmod 600 /swapfile
sudo mkswap /swapfile
sudo swapon /swapfile
```

### Port conflicts

Edit `docker/docker-compose.*.yml` files and change port mappings, e.g.:
```yaml
ports:
  - "5602:5601"  # Change host port from 5601 to 5602
```

## Support

- GitHub Issues: https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/osint-soc-platform/issues
- Documentation: See `docs/` directory
'''

with open(f"{base_dir}/QUICKSTART.md", "w") as f:
    f.write(quickstart)

print("✅ Created .env.example with all required variables")
print("✅ Created QUICKSTART.md")
